# My mouse has a pair of page back and forward side buttons and horizontal scrolling functionality that are not functional by default in my Linux guest,
# actually those buttons are only recognized if the mouse itself is detected as a usb device by the guest, which you can proove by typing:
# cat /proc/bus/input/devices
# and using: xev to check each mouse key number.


# Working Button Assignments for the MX Revolution
# Name  Xbindkeys Number
# Left click    b:1
# Right click   b:3
# Main Wheel press down b:2
# Main Wheel press left b:7
# Main Wheel press right b:6
# Second Wheel press down       b:17
# Second Wheel press forward    b:13
# Second Wheel press backward   b:15
# Button Up     b:9
# Button Down   b:8

# Second Wheel press backward (b:15) - Ctrl + Page Up (previous page)
"/usr/bin/xvkbd -text "\[Control_L]\[Page_Up]""
  m:0x0 + b:15

# Second Wheel press forward (b:13) - Ctrl + Page Down (next page)
"/usr/bin/xvkbd -text "\[Control_L]\[Page_Down]""
  m:0x0 + b:13

# Second Wheel press down (b:17) - Ctrl + W (close tab/window)
"/usr/bin/xvkbd -text "\[Control_L]\[w]""
  m:0x0 + b:17

# Main Wheel press left (b:6) - Ctrl + C (copy)
"/usr/bin/xvkbd -text "\[Control_L]\[c]""
  m:0x0 + b:6

# Main Wheel press right (b:7) - Ctrl + V (paste)
"/usr/bin/xvkbd -text "\[Control_L]\[v]""
  m:0x0 + b:7

# disable default Search for KRunner in KDE settings
# sudo evtest to confirm which search key is mapped to
# Map XF86Search (keycode 225 or 217) to simulate the middle mouse button click
"/usr/bin/xdotool mousedown 2 mouseup 2"
  XF86Search

